Notes: Late 19th and 20th century business and architectural records, 20th century maps, photographs, and newspapers; over 70 pieces of rolling stock including vintage steam locomotives, historic wooden cars, Pullmans (including the 1911 private car, 'Superb' used by President Harding), World War II troop kitchen, and 1940 railway post office.  Over 10 signifcant pieces of transit equipment from Atlanta's transit history.
